  "translations": {
    "en": "He said to his mother: 'Hand me the garment of hair, for I have realized that you two will lead me to ruin.' His mother gave him the garment and clung to him. Zakariyya said: 'O mother of Yahya! Let him go, for the veil has been lifted from the covering of his heart, and living a normal life will not benefit him.' So Yahya stood, put on his garment, placed the hooded robe on his head, then went to Bayt al-Maqdis and continued worshiping Allah, the Mighty and Majestic, with the rabbis, until what happened to him happened.",
